               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="187703050103"></xptr>
               <p>Anderson, and asked to inspect some patterns—he choose some, and directed them to be sent to some number in Commercial Street—he gave us as a reference, Wood, Laurie and Co., of Leadenhall Street, giving a number which I forget—I went there; the place was locked—I went again and saw Wood, who said Anderson and Co. were respectable people, and were trustworthy to the extent of 80<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. or 100<hi rend="italic">l</hi>., and his firm had done business with them for many years—I said "As their name is not in the directory would you kindly give me their previous address"—he made no direct answer—I asked where their firm had done business—he said they met in the street—I remarked that was a singular way of transacting business—he said he could not help it; it was so—we sent for the carpets and asked for the return of the patterns—on their return three were missing and have not since been returned; their value would be 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 15<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—I saw them at the Mansion House.</p>
               <p>
