                  </hi>. I am another daughter of the prisoner Cohen—I was with my sister when the dectives came on November 3rd and 4th—they examined the books and searched the place—O'Callaghan told Banks to make notes of everything, and my sister helped as he called out the goods—I cannot swear to the invoices; the detectives appeared satisfied with them—we have given directions to our man Ebrecht to find Hart.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined.</hi> I do not live at the Minories; I was there because we were busy, and father was in custody—I do not usually take part in the business—I was at home when a piano was brought in a van—I do not know either Hart or Harris.</p>
